    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Negotiate" id="id-652"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Negotiate" id="id-512"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C104"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Negotiate" id="id-2012">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S006"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with preparation, dialogue and reaching an agreement for the purpose of purchasing products or services. This includes understanding the product or service to purchase, knowing the seller, understanding bargaining positions of parties involved, fact finding meetings, internal reviews, bargaining meetings and debriefings.

General objectives of negotiation include:

Additional objectives of negotiation may include agreement on information exchange, inspection processes, flexibility.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Negotiate &amp; Award" id="id-2192">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S302"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Preparation, dialogue and reaching an agreement of terms and conditions and formal selection of the supplier for materials of services required to Make and/or Deliver Engineer-To-Order orders</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Notify Customer" id="id-432">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S403"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with receiving a return delivery. This includes the operator of the vehicle reporting to the receiving party, verification of the Return Authorization, unloading the vehicle, signing for the delivery and recording the receipt.

Receiveis aReverse Logisticsprocess. The receipt of the product or asset is recorded. Depending on the use case, ownership transfer may or may not occur.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Obtain Approvals" id="id-572"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Obtain Signatures" id="id-662"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C405"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Obtain Signatures" id="id-522"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C105"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Obtain Signatures" id="id-602"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C207"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pack" id="id-92">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D108"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packing or re-packing, and labeling products in preparation for shipment. This may include inserting or affixing invoices and import/export documentation. Re-packing is primarily done to protect the product packaging or product from downstream damage during transportation, storage and handling, but companies also use this to advertise their brands or limit the risk of theft</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pack" id="id-192">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D208"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packing or re-packing, and labeling products in preparation for shipment. This may include inserting or affixing invoices and import/export documentation. Re-packing is primarily done to protect the product packaging or product from downstream damage during transportation, storage and handling, but companies also use this to advertise their brands or limit the risk of theft</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pack" id="id-302">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D309"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packing or re-packing, and labeling products in preparation for shipment. This may include inserting or affixing invoices and import/export documentation. Re-packing is primarily done to protect the product packaging or product from downstream damage during transportation, storage and handling, but companies also use this to advertise their brands or limit the risk of theft</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pack" id="id-382">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packing or re-packing, and labeling products in preparation for shipment. This may include inserting or affixing invoices and import/export documentation. Re-packing is primarily done to protect the product packaging or product from downstream damage during transportation, storage and handling, but companies also use this to advertise their brands or limit the risk of theft</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Package" id="id-2392">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="M105"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packaging and labeling the product. This may include preparing the packaging, inserting the product in its packaging, sealing the packaging, applying product labels to the packaging and where necessary insert the packaged product in group packaging (e.g. bottled liquids in a carton).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Package" id="id-2472">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="M206"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packaging and labeling the product. This may include preparing the packaging, inserting the product in its packaging, sealing the packaging, applying product labels to the packaging and where necessary insert the packaged product in group packaging (e.g. bottled liquids in a carton).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Package" id="id-2562">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="M307"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Packaging and labeling the product. This may include preparing the packaging, inserting the product in its packaging, sealing the packaging, applying product labels to the packaging and where necessary insert the packaged product in group packaging (e.g. bottled liquids in a carton).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Perform Metrics Organizational Analysis" id="id-1022">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A112"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with reviewing the roles and responsibilities for the (high-level) metrics. Example tools include:t:RACI/ARCI, CAIRO, DACI charts.

At:RACIchart defines roles and responsibilities for supply chain KPI's for the purposes of analyzing conflicts, deficits, and to clarify for communication where various input/outputs are required.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Perform Network Organizational Analysis" id="id-1092">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with reviewing the roles and responsibilities at the network node level.

The objective of Network Organizational Analysis is to document roles and responsibilities for nodes and high level processes across the supply chain network for the purposes of analyzing conflicts and deficits, and to clarify for communication where various inputs/outputs are required.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Perform Process Organizational Analysis" id="id-1222">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A304"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with reviewing the roles and responsibilities at the detailed process level. The purpose of Process Organizational Analysis is to document roles and responsibilities for individual processes in the supply chain.

A RACI chart defines roles and responsibilities for supply chains for the purposes of analyzing conflicts, deficits, and to clarify for communication where various input/outputs are required.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Perform Supply Chain Organizational Analysis" id="id-962">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A106"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with reviewing the roles and responsibilities at the supply chain level.

Organizational analysis for the end-to-end supply chain defines roles and responsibilities for the complete supply chain for the purposes of analyzing conflicts, deficits and to clarify for communication where various input/outputs are required.

All roles identified in theSupply Chain Outline(A102) are typically included in the organizational analysis.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Perform Technology Organizational Analysis" id="id-1362">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with reviewing the roles and responsibilities of technology assets. This includes budget responsibility and vendor relationship management and contract management responsibilities. The objective of Technology Organizational Analysis is to document roles and responsibilities for technology (read: software and hardware instances) for the purpose of analyzing conflicts and deficits.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pick" id="id-82">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D107"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Locating, collecting, transferring and grouping products for orders in preparation of transportation. This may include scheduling picks, issuing pick instructions, picking the product in sequence of consumption or issuance and recording the completion of the pick process</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pick" id="id-182">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D207"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Locating, collecting, transferring and grouping products for orders in preparation of transportation. This may include scheduling picks, issuing pick instructions, picking the product in sequence of consumption or issuance and recording the completion of the pick process</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pick" id="id-292">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D308"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Locating, collecting, transferring and grouping products for orders in preparation of transportation. This may include scheduling picks, issuing pick instructions, picking the product in sequence of consumption or issuance and recording the completion of the pick process</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Pick" id="id-372">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D405"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Locating, collecting, transferring and grouping products for orders in preparation of transportation. This may include scheduling picks, issuing pick instructions, picking the product in sequence of consumption or issuance and recording the completion of the pick process</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Present Renewal" id="id-642"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C403"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Present Solution" id="id-462"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Present Solution" id="id-712"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A104"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Prioritize Network Metrics" id="id-1132">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A208"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the determination which performance gaps will be addressed in solution design. The purpose of this prioritization process is to ensure the organization is focused on the metrics that have (the highest) impact on the overall performance gap (i.e. cascading the performance goals into the organization).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Prioritize Root Causes" id="id-1502">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G104"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with developing a list of root causes that need to be addressed and sorting these from most to least important. This may include obtaining agreement and/or funding to initiate a formal improvement project - where applicable.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Prioritize Supply Chains" id="id-942">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="A104"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Determining the relative importance of supply chains and assignment of strategy management resources. Not all supply chains are of equal value to an organization</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Process Inquiry" id="id-122">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D201"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the receiving and responding to customer inquiries. This includes responding to inquiries on product configuration, availability, lead times, transportation costs and optionally temporary reserving resources.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Process Inquiry" id="id-22">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D101"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the receiving and responding to customer inquiries. This includes responding to inquiries on product availability, lead times, transportation costs.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Process Return Inquiry" id="id-2272">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S401"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with receiving, verifying and responding to an inquiry about the terms and conditions for product returns. This may include collecting case specific information, initial problem identification and offering options to the customer. An Inquiry may result in (trigger) theS402process.

Process Return Inquiryis aReverse Logisticsprocess.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Produce" id="id-2372">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M103"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with performing one or more tasks to convert raw materials, components, parts, or sub-assemblies into sellable products, sub-assemblies or semi-finished products.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Produce" id="id-2452">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with performing one or more tasks to convert raw materials, components, parts, or sub-assemblies into sellable products, sub-assemblies or semi-finished products. The product is produced for a specificCustomer Order. Production volumes are determined by the orders for which they are produced.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Produce" id="id-2542">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M305"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with performing one or more tasks to convert raw materials, components, parts, or sub-assemblies into sellable products, custom sub-assemblies or custom semi-finished products. The product is produced for a specificCustomer Orderbased on the order-engineering for this order. Production volumes are determined by the orders for which they are produced.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Propose Action" id="id-792">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A205"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the collection, validation and comparison of network-level practices to a baseline for standardization. This includes assessing the maturity (read: level and effectiveness) of the implementation of the 'standard' process.

The purpose of Network Standardization Analysis is to determine if and at what level the network configuration and the high level processes meet standardization requirements. It also assesses the maturity of the process category as a whole and provides a starting point for assessing potential improvements on supply chain processes.

Example approaches include: Best practice assessments, practice or process benchmarking. A Best Practice Assessment reviews preferred, best or desired practices for level-2 processes (e.g.P1,S1,M2,D3), and assess relevancy, degree of implementation.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Advisory" id="id-882">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A405"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the development of a document or collection of documents describing the specifications, relationships, models and guidelines of the technology required to automate the supply chain processes. The supply chain technology architecture is typically part of a larger IT or Enterprise architecture.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Distribution Plan" id="id-1942">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Approving, formatting and communicating the Distribution Plan. This may include a formal process to review and ratify the plan and/or identify alternative scenarios triggering a rerun of a recalculation with the intention to achieve a more favorable Distribution Plan</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Network Change Roadmap" id="id-1182">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A213"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with communicating the approved changes and priorities for specific supply chain networks. This may include changes in performance goals for node-level management and their organizations, chartering technology related departments.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Pricelist" id="id-502"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C103"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Process Change Portfolio" id="id-1322">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A314"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with communicating the approved changes and priorities for specific processes. This may include changes in performance goals for process-level management and their organizations, chartering technology related departments ΓÇösuch as ITΓÇö to source, develop, install and/or configure existing or new technology solutions.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Production Plan" id="id-1892">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P304"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Approving, formatting and communicating the Production Plan. This may include generating Production/Work Order Requisitions.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Resource Plan" id="id-1462">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A414"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>End-Of-Use Return</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Sourcing Plan" id="id-1842">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Approving, formatting and communicating the Materials Requirements Plan (MRP)</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Supply Chain Plan" id="id-1792">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P106"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Communicating the supply chain operations plan, gaps and corrective actions</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Publish Supply Chain Strategy" id="id-1052">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A115"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with formalizing supply chain strategy and communicating the strategy or updates to the strategy to the relevant organizations for the purpose of implementation of the strategy.

Generally the contents of supply chain strategy includes:

Publishing supply chain strategy generally happens multiple ways: management communication, business policies updates and/or establishing a task force (project team).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Put Away" id="id-2072">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S105"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receipt and put away product in general stock locations. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Put Away" id="id-2152">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S206"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receipt and put away product in general stock locations. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Put Away" id="id-2242">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S307"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receipt and put away product in general stock locations. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Put Away" id="id-2322">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receipt and put away product in general stock locations. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Put Away" id="id-72">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D106"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receipt and put away product in general stock locations. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive" id="id-2122">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S203"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the arrival, validation and acceptance of a shipment in preparation for unloading. This includes processing identification of the vehicle, verification of paperwork, weighing in, providing directions to the unloading area, assigning a position in the unloading queue and parking or queueing the vehicle, container, rail car.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive" id="id-2212">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S304"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the arrival, validation and acceptance of a shipment in preparation for unloading. This includes processing identification of the vehicle, verification of paperwork, weighing in, providing special instructions to the unloading area, assigning a position in the unloading queue and parking or queueing the vehicle, container, rail car.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive" id="id-2292">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S403"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with receiving a return delivery. This includes the operator of the vehicle reporting to the receiving party, verification of the Return Authorization, unloading the vehicle, signing for the delivery and recording the receipt.

Receiveis aReverse Logisticsprocess. The receipt of the product or asset is recorded. Depending on the use case, ownership transfer may or may not occur.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive" id="id-2042">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S102"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the arrival and acceptance of the vehicle. This includes processing identification of the vehicle, verification of paperwork, weighing in, providing directions to the unloading area, assigning a position in the unloading queue and parking the vehicle/container/rail car to await unloading to commence.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive &amp; Stage" id="id-172">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D206"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with receiving and putting away or staging product in Sales Order Stock. This includes determining the most appropriate storage location and making product pickable*.Make-to-Orderprocesses require product to be stored in order-specific locations as the product has been requested for such individual order.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive &amp; Stage" id="id-282">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D307"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with receiving, putting away and making product pickable. TheD3process typically requires product to be stored in order-specific locations, as product has been requested, produced, configured and optionally engineered for such individual order.

The physical movement and administrative flagging that product is pickable may take place at different times. This means that a product may be in the storage location from where picks take place, but may not have cleared final inspection, for example.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Claim" id="id-752">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A201"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the gathering and interpretation of supply chain strategy information. The purpose of supply chain strategy analysis is to understand the supply chains defined in the strategy layer and the prioritized performance gaps. Information collected includes: supply chain definitions, strategy goals and priorities by supply chain.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Inquiry" id="id-682">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A101"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with gathering and interpreting business plan information, including vision, mission, charter, plans (volume, growth, width, depth), management objectives, markets, products, customers, competitors, growth plans, and product positioning.

An organization's business plan provides a communication vehicle that structures the thinking about vision, mission, and charter of an enterprise, and then articulates the approach to supplying markets with products and services with the objective of specific financial goals. Competitive analysis, timeline, funding, and management objectives are usually included.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Request" id="id-542">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="C201"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receiving the renewal request from the customer or sales agent. This includes selecting the appropriate renewal method</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Request" id="id-622">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="C401"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receiving the renewal request from the customer or sales agent. This includes selecting the appropriate renewal method</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Request" id="id-482">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="C101"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receiving the renewal request from the customer or sales agent. This includes selecting the appropriate renewal method</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Request for Proposal" id="id-222">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D301"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the receiving, reviewing, and accepting or declining the invitation to aRFP. This includes obtaining the summary or full text of theRFP, understanding theRFPprocess and selecting whichRFP'sto respond to and may include responding to aPQQ.Inquiry-to-OrderQuote-to-CashDenied Party ListRequest for ProposalOrder Management Cost</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Receive Settlement" id="id-362">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with accepting, reconciling and recording the refund, discount, credit note and/or replacement for the returned product.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Recondition, Repair, Remake" id="id-2642">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the actual repair, remanufacture, refurbish, service or recycle the product or asset. The outcome of this process is a product or asset that is restored to the desired state ready for inspection or further examination.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Refine &amp; Negotiate" id="id-592"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C206"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Refresh Customer Needs" id="id-442">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with unloading the transportation vehicle or transportation and storage unit (e.g. Intermodal Containers). TheUnloadprocess may differ based on product characteristics -- like bulk materials or bulk liquids, individually packaged items or parts, palletized boxes. The process may include unboxing, de-palletizing and recording theGRwhere applicable.

Unloadis aReverse Logisticsprocess.Sourcing Cycle TimeDemurrage and DetentionGoods ReceiptSource-to-PayDock Appointment Scheduling</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Release Contract" id="id-532"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C106"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Release Contract" id="id-612"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C208"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Repackage" id="id-2662">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M408"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with packaging and labeling the product for the purpose of returning the product to inventory or the asset owner/user/lessee. This may include preparing the packaging, inserting the product in its packaging, sealing the packaging, applying product labels to the packaging and where necessary insert the packaged product in group packaging.

TheM4process may add multiple packagings:</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Report and Communicate" id="id-1732">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with collecting Sustainability data, creating Sustainability reports, and publishing status and progress on Sustainability initiatives.Environmental Sustainability RatioIntake Sustainability RatioRecovery RatioOutput Sustainability Ratio</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Report and Communicate" id="id-1532">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G107"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with communicating the project or program and reporting progress.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Report and Communicate" id="id-1602">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G207"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with ..</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Report and Communicate" id="id-1672">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G307"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with ..</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Request Return Authorization" id="id-342">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D402"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with requesting and receiving a return authorization from the seller. This may include recording the information in the related system of record and printing or retrieving a pre-approved return authorization.Deliver Cycle TimeService Return</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Reserve Inventory" id="id-42">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D103"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with identifying and reserving inventory or future inventory required to fulfill the order. This may include identifying inventory in multiple ship-from locations. This may include creating or updating scheduled shipment and/or delivery dates or availability dates for customer pickup.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Review Feedback" id="id-472">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S407"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with physically and/or logically moving and storing the returned process awaiting processing or disposal. This generally includes internal handling and transportation only. This includes recording inventory transactions and status changes as required.

Transferis aReverse Logisticsprocess.Sourcing Cycle TimeSource-to-PayWarehouse</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Route &amp; Schedule Order" id="id-142">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D203"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Determining the origin and requesting product for a customer order (routing) and determining the delivery date for the order (scheduling)</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Route Inquiry" id="id-692"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A102"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Run, Validate &amp; Distribute Reports" id="id-1472">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G101"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with scheduling and running reports, verifying data and distributing these reports.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Delivery &amp; Installation" id="id-262">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D305"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the scheduling of delivery resources and the selection of transportation mode, service provider and issuing a request for transportation services for product. This may include determining optimal transportation mode, route and service level to meet customer promise, building loads and tendering for transportation services. Typically transportation scheduling focuses on:

Delivery resource scheduling focuses on:

Once Delivery &amp; Installation Scheduling is complete the order may be updated with the latest delivery information and a notification may be send to the resources, transportation parties and/or the customer.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Make Orders" id="id-2432">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M202"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with validating material and production asset availability, assigning orders to production assets, sequencing production activities and monitoring and correcting production progress.

This is aM2process; Customer orders are the only type of demand and distinctly identifiable in the process. Planning primarily focuses on positioning capacity and scheduling primarily focuses on schedule adherence (as a change in the schedule impacts a customer order directly).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Project Resources" id="id-252">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D304"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with determining the resources required to deliver the project, requesting product and resources for the project order (routing) and determining the delivery date for the project order (scheduling). This may include placing a request or order for product or resources on the supplying entity (manufacturing, sourcing, delivery resources).</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Renewal" id="id-422">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S402"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Identifying the type of renewal, scheduling renewal sales activities and assigning sales resources</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Resources" id="id-2522">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="M303"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Developing the production schedule. This includes validating material and production resource availability, coordinating production activities, sequencing production activities and monitoring and correcting production progress.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Transportation" id="id-152">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the selection of transportation mode, service provider and issuing a request for transportation services. This may include determining optimal transportation mode, route and service level to meet customer promise, building loads and tendering for transportation services. Typically transportation scheduling focuses on:

Once transportation scheduling is complete the order may be updated with the latest delivery information and a notification (Schedule Change) may be send to the sending and/or receiving parties.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Transportation" id="id-52">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D104"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the selection ofTransportation Mode,Service Providerand issuing a request for transportation services. This may include determining optimalTransportation Mode(s), route and service level to meet customer promise, building loads and tendering for transportation services.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Transportation" id="id-352"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="D403"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Schedule Work Orders" id="id-2602">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M402"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with validating material and production asset availability, assigning orders to production assets, sequencing production activities and monitoring and correcting production progress. This may include issuing theWork Or Production Orders.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Segment Supply Chains" id="id-932">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="A103"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Dividing a business into subsets ('supply chains') of product/market combinations that have common needs. Supply chain segmentation is dependent upon product segmentation and market segmentation strategies and typically involves understanding product and market characteristics</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Settle Claim" id="id-812">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A207"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the gathering and analysis of performance gaps within the network. Information collected includes: Performance (metrics) by node and high-level process in the network.

The purpose of Network Performance Analysis is to identify the processes that have the highest contribution to the overall performance gap.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Settle Return" id="id-2342">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S408"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with processing and communicating the settlement to the customer. This may include:

The processes of entering a replacement order and product return to the customer are part of theDeliverprocess, the processes of creating aM4order is part of theMakeprocess.

Settle Returnis aRLprocess.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Ship" id="id-112">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D110"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The physical transportation of product between locations. This may include customs clearance and duty processing. This process may be highly customized to support the unique requirements of Engineer-to-Order products and services</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Ship" id="id-212">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D210"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The physical transportation of product between locations. This may include customs clearance and duty processing. This process may be highly customized to support the unique requirements of Engineer-to-Order products and services</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Ship" id="id-322">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D311"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The physical transportation of product between locations. This may include customs clearance and duty processing. This process may be highly customized to support the unique requirements of Engineer-to-Order products and services</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Ship" id="id-402">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D408"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The physical transportation of product between locations. This may include customs clearance and duty processing. This process may be highly customized to support the unique requirements of Engineer-to-Order products and services</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Submit Proposal" id="id-582"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C205"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Tender" id="id-2002">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S005"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Preparing, inviting, receiving, reviewing and selecting bids or proposals from suppliers and outsourcing partners. This may include understanding the product or service to purchase, developing the tendering conditions and advertising the tender</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2412">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M107"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with movement of product (FG, semi-finished goods, assemblies, subassemblies) to theDeliverprocess or anotherMakeprocess. This may includeBackflushingof materials used, recording the Make completions, calculating and recording production costs and closing the production order where applicable.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2082">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S106"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the movement and handover of product (goods, materials) to a process requesting replenishment. E.g. a request to replenish production line stock. This includes scheduling the transfer, picking, handling of the product and recording the associated inventory transactions.

Products transferred usingS106areGeneric Stock(unrestricted stock) unless picked, assigned and received for a specific (production) order.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2492">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M208"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with movement of product (finished goods, semi-finished goods, assemblies, subassemblies) to the Deliver process or another Make process. This may includeBackflushingof materials used, recording the Make completions, recording/calculating production costs and closing the production order where applicable.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2162">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S207"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the movement and handover of product (goods, materials) to the process originating the sourcing request for the product (e.g.Make-to-OrderorDeliver-to-Order). This includes scheduling the transfer, picking, handling of the product and recording the associated inventory transactions.

Products transferred usingSource-to-Orderprocesses areSales Order Stock: sourced for a specific customer order and/or production order.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2252">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S308"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the movement and handover of product (goods, materials) to the process originating the sourcing of the product (e.g.Make-To-Engineering-OrderorDeliver-To-Engineering-Order). This includes scheduling the transfer, picking, handling of the product and recording the associated inventory transactions.

Products transferred usingSource-to-Engineering-Orderprocesses are customSales Order Stock: sourced based on a specification derived from a specificCustomer Orderand/orProduction Order.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2332">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S407"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with physically and/or logically moving and storing the returned process awaiting processing or disposal. This generally includes internal handling and transportation only. This includes recording inventory transactions and status changes as required.

Transferis aReverse Logisticsprocess.Sourcing Cycle TimeSource-to-PayWarehouse</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2582">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M309"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with movement of product (finished goods, semi-finished goods, assemblies, subassemblies) to theDeliverprocess or anotherMakeprocess. This may includeBFof materials used, recording the Make completions, recording/calculating production costs and closing the production order where applicable.

Products transferred usingTransferprocesses areSales Order Stock: Product has been requested, produced, configured and optionally engineered for such individual order.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-2682">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="M410"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with movement of products (finished goods, semi-finished goods, assemblies, subassemblies) or assets to theDeliverprocess or anotherMprocess. This may includeBFof materials used, recording theM4completions, recording/calculating production costs and closing theWOwhere applicable.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Transfer" id="id-722"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A105"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Treat Risks" id="id-1652">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="G305"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Identification, conceptual design and concept testing for solutions that will address the risk exceeding the Risk Appetite</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Treat Sustainability Gaps" id="id-1712">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="Stub description in original (name echoed)"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="G404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with ..</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Unload" id="id-2052">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S103"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with unloading the transportation vehicle. This may include inspection for damage, counting or weighing out to determine delivered volumes, taking samples for analysis and depalletizing, unpacking, repacking, repalletizing where needed.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Unload" id="id-2132">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S204"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with unloading the transportation vehicle. This may include inspection for damage, counting or weighing out to determine delivered volumes, taking samples for analysis and depalletizing, unpacking, repacking, repalletizing where needed.

An important part of aSource-to-Orderprocess is the ability to track the order specifics. This requires the purchase order number, production order number or customer order number to be recorded from this process onward. This inventory is typically consideredSales Order Stock.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Unload" id="id-2222">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S305"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with unloading the transport vehicle or container. The unload process may differ based on product characteristics - bulk materials or bulk liquids, individually packaged items or parts, palletized boxes. The process includes de-palletizing where necessary.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Unload" id="id-2302">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="S404"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with unloading the transportation vehicle or transportation and storage unit (e.g. Intermodal Containers). TheUnloadprocess may differ based on product characteristics -- like bulk materials or bulk liquids, individually packaged items or parts, palletized boxes. The process may include unboxing, de-palletizing and recording theGRwhere applicable.

Unloadis aReverse Logisticsprocess.Sourcing Cycle TimeDemurrage and DetentionGoods ReceiptSource-to-PayDock Appointment Scheduling</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Update Contract" id="id-672"><property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="C406"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Validate &amp; Create Order" id="id-132">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D202"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Receiving, validating and entering orders for Make-to-Order products and services. This may include configuring the product and validating the existence and accuracy of customer data (sold-to, ship-to), pricing information, customer credit and product/item numbers</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Validate Demand Forecast" id="id-1752">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P102"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Review of the consolidated demand forecast in order to reach an (unconstrained) consensus demand forecast for products and services</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Validate To-Be Network Design" id="id-1162">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A211"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with the testing and verification of proposed network changes. This includes testing functional design and verification against business policies, objectives and other decision criteria.

Tools: Risk Scenario Testing, Environmental Impact Study, Simulation.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:BusinessProcess" name="Validate To-Be Processes" id="id-1272">
      <property key="ORWiki-Issue" value="No description in original ORWiki source"/><property key="SCOR-ID" value="A309"/><property key="Level" value="3"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>The activities associated with developing and implementing tests to verify the proposed process changes can be implemented. Verification generally consists of three types of tests: feasibility (is it possible to implement), desirability (is it aligned with internal/external policies) and scalability (is it able to support the required number of transactions).</documentation>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Application" id="id-1bec76133e3f45e28558ff98c65ccbb8" type="application"/>
  <folder name="Technology &amp; Physical" id="id-3885907fa262407598361f991eeb6462" type="technology"/>
  <folder name="Motivation" id="id-cd5f5779f4354fcf930a6a1e2f13aaae" type="motivation"/>
  <folder name="Implementation &amp; Migration" id="id-6a24449cc66e4ae9ad9b87cb93cf2e49" type="implementation_migration"/>
  <folder name="Other" id="id-97192f45781b474589432fe45230e007" type="other">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="D Deliver" id="id-grp-deliver">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="D"/><property key="Level" value="1"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Deliveris the macro process representing the processes associated with managing orders and shipments for products and services. Deliver processes are required for supply chains to acceptt:SOs, fulfill these orders and invoice customers. Customers generally primarily interact with a supply chain throughDeliverprocesses.

TheDeliverprocess includes order management, warehousing, transportation, managing Import/Export.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="E Enable" id="id-grp-enable">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="E"/><property key="Level" value="1"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>SCOR Enable domain - Enabling capabilities (Align, Manage, Sell, Contract, Assist)</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="M Make" id="id-grp-make">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="M"/><property key="Level" value="1"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Makeis the macro process representing the processes associated with creating, manufacturing and/or repairing products.Makeincludes activities classified as discrete manufacturing, process manufacturing andMaintenance, Repair And Overhaultype of transformation processes.

Makeprocesses convert input materials/products into output products/materials depending on the supply chain configuration:

Customization describes a Manufacturing process that requires information provided by the customer to define the product configuration orOrder Engineeringrequirements.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="P Plan" id="id-grp-plan">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="P"/><property key="Level" value="1"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Planis the macro process representing the processes associated with establishing an estimation of volumes and/or revenue for current and future periods (the plan) and determining the actions required to achieve 'the plan'. Planning is an iterative process, balancing supply and demand in order to position materials, products and/or capacity to achieve 'the plan'.

Balancing is a process of matching demand to supply. The output of balancing are three lists:

The demand shortage and supply shortage lists typically drive initiatives to find additional volume/revenue opportunities (chasing supply or demand), allowing for the volume/revenue estimate to improve in subsequent iterations of the plan.

The scope and importance ofPlanprocesses depends on the supply chain configuration.Make-to-Stockprocesses depend heavily onPlanprocesses; getting the mix of item numbers correct may make or break the ability to achieve the revenue goals. For non-Make-To-Stock processes (Make-to-Order,Engineer-to-Order,Reverse Logistics) getting capacity right is generally more important.</documentation>
    </element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:Grouping" name="S Source" id="id-grp-source">
      <property key="SCOR-ID" value="S"/><property key="Level" value="1"/><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/><documentation>Sourceis the macro process representing the processes associated with ordering and receiving products and services. This includes scheduling, receiving, inspecting and approving payment, and optionally identify and qualify suppliers, for products (materials, semi-finished goods, goods, merchandize) and services.

TheSourceprocess includesPurchase OrderManagement and Inbound Operations.</documentation>
    </element>
  </folder>
  <folder name="Relations" id="id-857dbcdcef91448f8dca6577acd61fb6" type="relations">
    <element xsi:type="archimate:CompositionRelationship" id="id-comp-plan-1" source="id-grp-plan" target="id-691"><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
    <element xsi:type="archimate:CompositionRelationship" id="id-comp-plan-2" source="id-grp-plan" target="id-701"><property key="Source" value="ORWiki"/></element>
